value.value: A uterine adnexa cancer that is located_in the parametrium.
A uterine cancer that is located_in the adnexa.
A uterine adnexa cancer that is located_in the round ligament.
A pertussis that is a milder disease caused by the bacterium Bordetella parapertussis. The disease has_symptom coughing, has_symptom sneezing, or has_symptom runny nose.
An eye degenerative disease that is characterized by intraocular iron toxicity typically due to a retained foreign body.
A common bile duct disease characterized by the presence of at least one gallstone in the common bile duct.
A microcytic anemia that is characterized by pallor, fatigue, lightheadedness, and weakness and has_material_basis_in low total body iron causing impaired synthesis of red blood cells.

An anemia that is characterized by a decrease in the ratio of the weight of hemoglobin to the volume of the erythrocyte. As a result, the red cells have an area of central pallor which is increased in size. The leading cause is iron deficiency.
A lower respiratory tract disease that affects the airways leading into the lungs, which is caused due to inflammation of the bronchi and bronchioles, infection, or blockage.
An osteochondrosis that results_in death and collapse located_in navicular bone of foot.

A glaucoma that is characterized by a total loss of vision, uncontrolled pressure in the eye, severe pain in the eye, absence of pupillary light reflex, absence of pupillary response, and the eye has a stony appearance.
A refractive error characterized by the optics of the eye to focus a point object into a sharp focused image on the retina, has_symptom blurred vision.
A laryngitis in which symptoms last longer than three weeks. Gastroesophageal reflux, and lingering bronchitis can cause the disease.
A pericardium disease that is characterized by an abnormal accumulation of fluid in the pericardial cavity.

A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by inadequate dietary protein and calories, which can have profound systemic effects including decreased metabolism, altered tissue distribution, compromised immunity, and impaired growth, and has_material_basis_in dietary deprivation.
A sarcoma and malignant neoplasm of urinary bladder that is located_in the bladder.
A urinary system cancer that is located_in the ureter.
An acute kidney failure that is characterized by severe renal vasoconstriction.
A syndrome that is characterized by papulonodular skin lesions containing a proliferation of true macrophages associated with arthritis.
A refractive error characterized by the inability to see farther objects clearly.
A bone development disease where one or both are inclined inwards, axially rotated outwards, and pointing downwards with concomitant soft tissue abnormalities.
A sarcoma and malignant neoplasm of penis that is located_in the penis.
A nephrosis characterized by marked increase in glomerular protein permeability resulting in marked elevation of urine protein levels, hypoalbuminemia, hyperlipidemia, and hypercoagulability.
